Package com.samju.hospital.controller

Class OperationalController

java.lang.Object
com.samju.hospital.controller.OperationalController
@CrossOrigin @RestController @RequestMapping("/api") public class OperationalController extends Object
The OperationalController class defines RESTful endpoints for creating operational records in the hospital management system. It is annotated with RestController to indicate that it is a Spring MVC controller for handling HTTP requests.

Endpoints in this controller include:

  • /api/doctor: Create a new doctor report.
  • /api/nurse: Create a new nurse report.
  • /api/lab: Create a new laboratory test.
  • /api/pharmacy: Create a new pharmacy record for drug administration.
  • /api/radiology: Create a new radiology scan.
  • /api/account: Create a new account record for billing.

Usage example: 

 
 public class SomeClient {
     // Example usage of the RESTful endpoints provided by OperationalController
 }
